# Feedback AI Platform

This repository contains the full-stack implementation of the Feedback AI Analysis Platform, including:

- Frontend (Analyzer_BE) built using Angular 18
- Backend (Analyzer_FE) built using .NET 8 Web API + EF Core

- AI Integration powered by OpenAI GPT-4o-mini

The system allows users to:

Submit feedback

Automatically analyze it using AI

Assign system-level tags & priorities

View feedback lists, filters, and full details

## Prerequisites

Before running the project, ensure the following are installed on your machine:

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (v18+),
- [Angular CLI](https://angular.io/cli) (v18+)

- [.NET 8 SDK & .NET Tools](https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download/dotnet/8.0)

- [PgAdmin](https://www.pgadmin.org/download/) (pgAdmin 4)

- [Visual Studio Code](https://code.visualstudio.com/) or any IDE
- [Postman](https://www.postman.com/) (optional for API testing)

- [OpenAI Platform Account](https://platform.openai.com/) (for API Key)

###### If you are having any difficulties setting up, dont hesitate to ask me as i can walk you .through the whole setup

---

## Getting Started

- The following commands assume you are in the root of the project folder (`Analyzer`)

Open the terminal and run the following commands to set up your frontend.

```bash
# Navigate to the specno front-end
cd Analyzer_FE
```

```bash
# Install dependencies
npm install
```

Update environment file:

src/environments/environment.ts

export const environment = {
production: false,
apiUrl: 'https://localhost:5034'
};

```bash
# Serve the frontend
ng serve
```

Angular will run at:

http://localhost:4200

### 4. Run the Back-End

Navigate to folder (`Analyzer_BE/FeedbackAnalyzer`) dir, run the following commands to set up your backend services

```bash
# Clean the project
dotnet clean
```

```bash
# Install dependencies
dotnet restore
```

```bash
# Build the solution
dotnet build
```

Update environment file:

FeedbackAnalyzer/appsettings.json

Replace {userName} with your db server username and {Password} with your password.
Replace {API_KEY} with your open AI API key.

{
"ConnectionStrings": {
"DefaultConnection": "Host=localhost;Port=5432;Database=Anlayzer;Username={userName};Password={Password}"
},
"OpenAI": {
"ApiKey": "API_KEY",
"Model": "gpt-4o-mini",
"BaseUrl": "https://api.openai.com/"
},
"Logging": {
"LogLevel": {
"Default": "Information",
"Microsoft.AspNetCore": "Warning"
}
},
"AllowedHosts": "\*"
}

```bash
# Initialize your Db
dotnet ef database update
```

```bash
# Run the service
dotnet run
```
